# Documentation — read and maintain

## Before changing API or user-visible behaviour

1. Skim [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) doc map.
2. Update the **lowest complexity** doc that covers the feature.

## After changes — update when relevant

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New domain term or invariant | [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) |
| New/changed UI route | [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md) |
| New/changed UI element (class, component, pattern) | [ui-elements-gallery.md](../../docs/ui-elements-gallery.md) |
| Flat UI / visual language change | [ui-elements-gallery.md](../../docs/ui-elements-gallery.md) § Flat UI + [issues-ux.mdc](issues-ux.mdc) |
| Package, API surface, patterns | [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) |
| Doc debt closed | [conventions-checklist.md](../../docs/conventions-checklist.md) |
| New/changed user-facing feature | [README.md](../../README.md) § Features — see [readme.mdc](readme.mdc) |
| README badges or project name | [README.md](../../README.md) |

## Complexity order

1. **domain-specification** — vocabulary and rules
2. **feature-catalog** — routes and click paths
3. **ui-elements-gallery** — reusable UI components and patterns
4. **ARCHITECTURE** — technical structure
5. **README** — pitch and links

## Quality bar

- No stale type names after renames — grep docs when renaming.
- Cross-link; avoid duplicating large blocks.

